# Learnings for <skill-name>

OPTIONAL sidecar — recommended for generative/judgment skills. Two roles in
one file:

1. **Distilled lessons** (top) — permanent, curated guidance from real runs
   that shapes how the skill should behave. Loaded on demand like any
   reference doc; link it from SKILL.md.
2. **Retro log** (bottom) — a raw, capture-only backlog of per-run
   observations. Entries are **never auto-applied to SKILL.md**: a single run
   is n=1, not enough to justify a durable edit. `/improving-skills` reads the
   `Status: open` entries to seed candidate edits; a human or that loop decides
   what graduates. As entries are addressed, fold the durable ones up into
   "Distilled lessons" and prune the raw entry — that keeps this file curated
   and under the 200-line reference budget (Check 16).

## Distilled lessons

<Permanent, evidence-backed guidance. Start empty; fill from the retro log as
patterns repeat across runs. Each lesson should cite the runs behind it.>

## Retro log

Append one entry per retro (newest first). Keep it terse.

### YYYY-MM-DD — <one-line run summary>

- Worked: <what the skill did well — keep doing it>
- Inefficient / friction: <what was slow, repeated, or confusing>
- Candidate edit: <a specific, testable change — NOT applied here>
- New test? <a tests.md scenario this run revealed, or "none">
- Status: open | addressed (iter N / commit <sha>) | rejected (<why>)
